 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🧠 Mental Health Text Analysis — Feature Engineered Dataset\n",
    "### Data Science Assignment Notebook\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-problem-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Problem Statement\n",
    "\n",
    "Mental health disorders such as Anxiety, Depression, and Suicidal ideation are increasingly expressed through online text, yet remain under-diagnosed in the real world. This project analyzes a feature-engineered mental health text dataset to understand **what linguistic and sentiment patterns distinguish different mental health conditions**, so that early intervention systems can be designed more effectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset:** `mental_heath_feature_engineered.csv`  \n",
    "**Source:** Kaggle / open NLP mental health dataset (feature-engineered version)  \n",
    "**Rows × Columns:** 49,612 rows × 21 columns  \n",
    "\n",
    "### Column Descriptions\n",
    "| Column | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `Unique_ID` | Row identifier |\n",
    "| `text` | Raw input text written by the person |\n",
    "| `status` | Mental health label: *Anxiety, Normal, Depression, Suicidal* |\n",
    "| `text_length` | Normalized length of the text (0–1) |\n",
    "| `word_count` | Normalized number of words |\n",
    "| `num_urls` | Number of URLs in the text |\n",
    "| `num_emojis` | Number of emojis used |\n",
    "| `num_special_chars` | Count of special characters |\n",
    "| `num_excess_punct` | Excessive punctuation count (!!!, ???) |\n",
    "| `avg_word_length` | Average length of words used |\n",
    "| `stopword_ratio` | Fraction of words that are stopwords |\n",
    "| `type_token_ratio` | Vocabulary diversity ratio |\n",
    "| `polarity` | Sentiment polarity (0=negative, 1=positive) |\n",
    "| `subjectivity` | How subjective the text is (0=objective, 1=subjective) |\n",
    "| `noun_ratio` | Proportion of nouns |\n",
    "| `verb_ratio` | Proportion of verbs |\n",
    "| `adj_ratio` | Proportion of adjectives |\n",
    "| `adv_ratio` | Proportion of adverbs |\n",
    "| `has_suicidal_keyword` | Boolean — contains suicidal keywords |\n",
    "| `has_stress_keyword` | Boolean — contains stress-related keywords |\n",
    "| `has_help_keyword` | Boolean — contains help-seeking keywords |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-imports-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Import Libraries\n",
    "\n",
    "All required libraries are imported in a single cell below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-imports",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Standard data manipulation\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualization\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Machine learning\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display settings\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 25)\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='Set2')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('All libraries imported successfully!')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-imports-explain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**pandas** and **numpy** handle data loading and numerical operations. **matplotlib** and **seaborn** are used for all charts. **scikit-learn** provides the train/test split, label encoding, the Random Forest classifier, and accuracy metrics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-load-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Load & Explore the Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-load",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('mental_heath_feature_engineered.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Shape:', df.shape)\n",
    "print('\\nFirst 5 rows:')\n",
    "display(df.head())\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nColumn Data Types:')\n",
    "print(df.dtypes)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-load-explain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The dataset has **49,612 rows and 21 columns**. Most feature columns are `float64` (normalized numeric values). The `status`, `text`, and the three boolean keyword columns are stored as `object` (string) type."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-cleaning-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Data Cleaning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-missing",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check missing values\n",
    "print('Missing values per column:')\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
    "print(f'\\nTotal missing values: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\n",
    "print(f'Total rows with at least one NaN: {df.isnull().any(axis=1).sum()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-missing-explain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**9,600 rows** are missing values across nearly all feature columns (but NOT in `text` or `status`). This suggests a batch of rows where feature engineering was not completed — not random missingness. Because the `status` label is always present, we can safely **drop these incomplete rows** rather than imputing, since imputing 9,600 rows of multi-column NaN could introduce significant noise."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-drop-missing",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Drop rows where numeric features are missing\n",
    "df_clean = df.dropna(subset=['polarity', 'subjectivity', 'word_count', 'text_length']).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Rows before cleaning: {len(df)}')\n",
    "print(f'Rows after dropping NaN rows: {len(df_clean)}')\n",
    "print(f'Rows removed: {len(df) - len(df_clean)}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check for duplicates\n",
    "dupes = df_clean.duplicated().sum()\n",
    "print(f'\\nDuplicate rows: {dupes}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-drop-explain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After dropping the 9,600 incomplete rows we are left with **40,012 clean rows** — still a large, representative sample. No duplicate rows were found, so no further removal was needed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-fix-booleans",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fix boolean columns stored as strings\n",
    "bool_cols = ['has_suicidal_keyword', 'has_stress_keyword', 'has_help_keyword']\n",
    "for col in bool_cols:\n",
    "    df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].map({'True': True, 'False': False}).fillna(False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Boolean columns fixed:')\n",
    "print(df_clean[bool_cols].dtypes)\n",
    "print('\\nSample:')\n",
    "display(df_clean[bool_cols].head(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-fix-booleans-explain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The three keyword flag columns were stored as string `'True'`/`'False'` values instead of actual Python booleans. We convert them to proper boolean dtype so they work correctly in modeling and aggregations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-stats-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Descriptive Statistics (Numeric Columns)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-stats",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def describe_column(series, name):\n",
    "    print(f'\\n--- {name} ---')\n",
    "    print(f'  Mean:     {series.mean():.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'  Median:   {series.median():.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'  Mode:     {series.mode()[0]:.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'  Std Dev:  {series.std():.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'  Variance: {series.var():.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'  Range:    {series.max() - series.min():.4f}')\n",
    "    print(f'  Midrange: {(series.max() + series.min()) / 2:.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "describe_column(df_clean['polarity'],     'Polarity (Sentiment)')\n",
    "describe_column(df_clean['subjectivity'], 'Subjectivity')\n",
    "describe_column(df_clean['word_count'],   'Word Count (normalized)')\n",
    "describe_column(df_clean['text_length'],  'Text Length (normalized)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-stats-explain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Polarity** has a mean of ~0.50, meaning the average text is roughly neutral in sentiment. **Subjectivity** has a mean of ~0.45, indicating texts lean slightly more objective than subjective overall. **Word count** and **text length** both show high standard deviations relative to their means, reflecting that some posts are very short while others are very long."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-cleaning-summary-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 📋 Data Cleaning Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "| Issue Found | Action Taken | Reason |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| 9,600 rows had NaN in all feature columns | Dropped those rows | Feature engineering was not applied to them; imputation would be unreliable |\n",
    "| 3 boolean columns stored as strings | Converted to Python `bool` type | Ensures correct behavior in ML models and aggregations |\n",
    "| 0 duplicate rows | No action needed | Dataset was already deduplicated |\n",
    "\n",
    "Final clean dataset: **40,012 rows × 21 columns**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-viz-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Visualizations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-hist-md",
